body.description: MASTERFAN MF120 HALO WHITE EDITIONMasterFan MF120 Halo Gen2 ARGB case fan, a new series to the MasterFan family, provides a specific air cooling solution ideal for CPU coolers and chassis in-take fans. With dual Loop Addressable Gen 2 RGB Lighting ensuring the most vibrant display of Color for your coverage and generate high pressure airflow. MF120 Halo white edition is fitted with multiple layers of our exclusive noise reduction technologies and a perfect blend of fan blade design that put together work in harmony to cool your entire case and its components in silence.SPECIFICATIONSFAN PROFILES: ADDRESSABLE GEN 2 RGBFAN SPEED： 650-1800 RPM (PWM) ± 10%FAN AIRFLOW：47.2 CFM ± 10%FAN AIR PRESSURE： 1.6 MMH2O ± 10%FAN NOISE LEVEL ： 6 - 30 DBAFAN DIMENSIONS (L X W X H)： 120 X 120 X 25 MM / 4.7 X 4.7 X 1 INCHFAN MTTF： 160,000 HOURSFAN BEARING TYPE： RIFLE BEARINGFAN POWER CONNECTOR： 4-PIN (PWM)FAN RATED VOLTAGE： 12VDCFAN RATED CURRENT： 0.25AFAN SAFETY CURRENT： 0.37ARGB CONNECTOR： 3-PINRGB RATED VOLTAGE： 5V DCRGB RATED CURRENT： 0.55A (0.8A MAX)FAN POWER CONSUMPTION： 3.0WFAN WEIGHT： 180G / 0.4LBSSERIES： MASTERFANCOOLER TYPE： CASE FANFAN SIZE： 120FAN - LED LIGHTING： ARGB

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Bright, clean RGB.
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Got these to fill my jonsbo d31. Fans are very easy to connect and get working with the coolermaster software, or will synce to you mobo rgb controll. Fans are nice and quiet and give great airflow. Probably going to buy some 140mm soon to put on my 280mm cpu cooler. Love these Fans!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice budget fans w/ heavenly visuals!
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I saw these fans and just didn't know what to expect. After installing them into a computer with an older mobo (one without argb, the argument controller somehow didn't work. Once I got a mobo upgrade, I had access to argb headers, and they flipped on and Immediately thought "wow, these are better than I imagined". There was a bit of "apoxy" or adhesive on one of blades but so far there hasn't been any noticeable problems. The fans themselves cool pretty well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great looking fans, tedious software.
reviews.reviewText: The fans look fantastic, however the Coolermaster software is not the best I've worked with. After sometime of playing around with it though and figuring things out it become less of a hassle.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2023

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Unsure at this moment
reviews.reviewText: I have powered the fans up on a new mobo w/o a cpu. Really quiet but seem to be running a lowest speed, perhaps that can be changed once a cpu is installed. The lighting is very nice but again not able to the patterns not having a mobo program. The controller has no way to change, it seems to just be a hub to connect and fire up.As for Coolermaster itself, it appears this company has fallen off the face of the earth, absolutely no way to contact them or ask questions. All links to them is non working!...IMHO this company no longer exists!! So, with that said, I highly doubt I will buy any CM products, except for fans, which are easily replaceable and not a major expense, but for other products....NO WAY at this moment!

reviews.reviewTitle: Beau look pas de bruit très efficace
Looks good, but lacks information in add
reviews.reviewText: What I like: it has an easy to use Argb system with some of the best lighting ever on a 120mm fan, while still being amazingly quiet.What I dislike: there was no indication on the product whether it is intake or exhaust. I feel like this product could have been way better if either both sides looked the same, or there was options to make 2 intake and 1 exhaust. (When facing the aesthetically pleasing direction, it’s exhaust) If there is please let me know.Other than a backwards fan, looks awesome!
Es muy buen servicio, totalmente original y funcional, con trato amable.
